# Cursor Rules for Multi-Tool AI Agent

## Code Style
- Use ES modules (import/export) throughout
- Async/await over callbacks or raw Promises
- Descriptive variable names; no abbreviations
- Add JSDoc comments to all exported functions

## Architecture Rules
- All tool definitions go in src/tools/
- Never put API keys in code; always use process.env
- Every tool call MUST be logged with winston (tool name, input args, result summary)
- The agent must never expose raw stack traces to the UI

## LangChain Conventions
- Use createReactAgent from langchain/agents
- Memory: BufferWindowMemory with k=10
- All tools must extend DynamicTool or StructuredTool
- Tool descriptions must be specific enough for the LLM to choose correctly

## Documentation
- Update changelog.md with every meaningful change
- Keep roadmap.md checkboxes current
- context.md must always reflect the current state of the project

## Git
- .env is always gitignored
- node_modules, chroma_db/, *.log are gitignored
- Do NOT gitignore: .cursorrules, ai/, aiDocs/, CLAUDE.md, .cursor/
